  "texts": [
    "As shown in Table 3, mid-sized ViT-Base achieves a lower NC2 (closer to the ETF ideal) than both ViT-Small and the much larger ViT-Large.",
    "This analysis supports the view that the Climb corresponds to the formation of a collapsed classifier, but also raises a question about our non-monotonic scaling result: why does mid-sized ViT-Base achieve such favorable geometric structure?",
    "Answering this requires moving beyond a purely geometric description to a more mechanistic one.",
    "In the following section, we analyze the underlying information flow of the attention graph to better understand the computational processes that appear to underlie this transition, in particular how the trained model effectively bypasses parts of its nominal architectural design.",
    "Two decoder architectures help characterize the network's communication strategy."
  ]
